<div class="page-header">
  <h1>Buttons <small>grouping buttons</small></h1>
</div>

<p>
  Buttons can also be grouped together into individual groups, or full toolbars.  For individual button groups, you simply wrap a series of button elements in a div with the 
  <code>btn-group</code> class applied to it as follows:
</p>

<div class="btn-group">
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 1</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 2</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 3</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 4</button>
</div>
<br/><br/>

<pre>
  &lt;div class="btn-group"&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 1&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 2&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 3&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 4&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

<p>
  To combine button groups into a toolbar is as simple as wrapping your individual button groups in a div with the <code>btn-toolbar</code> class applied to it as follows:
</p>

<div class="btn-toolbar">
  <div class="btn-group">
    <button class="btn btn-info">1</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">2</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">3</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">4</button>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-group">
    <button class="btn btn-warning">5</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">6</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">7</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">8</button>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-group">
    <button class="btn btn-success">9</button>
  </div>
</div>

<pre>
  &lt;div class="btn-toolbar"&gt;
    &lt;div class="btn-group"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;1&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;2&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;3&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;4&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="btn-group"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;5&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;6&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;7&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;8&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="btn-group"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-success"&gt;9&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

<p>
  You can also make your button groups appear vertical, simply by adding the class <code>btn-group-vertical</code> along side the <code>btn-group</code> that's already there.
</p>

<div class="btn-toolbar">
  <div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical">
    <button class="btn btn-info">1</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">2</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">3</button>
    <button class="btn btn-info">4</button>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical">
    <button class="btn btn-warning">5</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">6</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">7</button>
    <button class="btn btn-warning">8</button>
  </div>

  <div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical">
    <button class="btn btn-success">9</button>
  </div>
</div>

<pre>
  &lt;div class="btn-toolbar"&gt;
    &lt;div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;1&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;2&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;3&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;4&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;5&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;6&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;7&lt;/button&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-warning"&gt;8&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

    &lt;div class="btn-group btn-group-vertical"&gt;
      &lt;button class="btn btn-success"&gt;9&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

<p>
  One of the more interesting things you can do with buttons & button groups is to make batches of toggle buttons, that behave like checkboxes and radio buttons. 
  For this to work correctly however you need to make sure you either include bootstrap.js (or the min version) or any of the seperate js files from a custom download 
  as this functionality requires javascript.  To create a single toggle button you only need to add a custom data attribute of <code>data-toggle="button"</code> to 
  your single button as follows:
</p>

<button class="btn btn-success" data-toggle="button">I'm a toggle button, click me</button>
<br/><br/>

<pre>
  &lt;button class="btn btn-success" data-toggle="button"&gt;I'm a toggle button, click me&lt;/button&gt;
</pre>

<p>
  It's just as easy to extend that toggle behaviour to your entire button group.  Simply create your group as we did previously but add a data-toggle of <code>buttons-checkbox</code> to the group div:
</p>

<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons-checkbox">
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 1</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 2</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 3</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 4</button>
</div>
<br/><br/>

<pre>
  &lt;div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons-checkbox"&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 1&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 2&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 3&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 4&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

<p>
  As the name suggests you can see the behaviour is the same as that of a collection of check boxes, this is no mistake as the intended use is to make good looking checkbox lists.  It may not surprise you 
  to learn that there's also a data-toggle called <code>buttons-radio</code> which as you can guess makes your button group behave like a set of radio buttons:
</p>

<div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons-radio">
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 1</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 2</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 3</button>
  <button class="btn btn-info">Button Number 4</button>
</div>
<br/><br/>

<pre>
  &lt;div class="btn-group" data-toggle="buttons-radio"&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 1&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 2&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 3&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button class="btn btn-info"&gt;Button Number 4&lt;/button&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
</pre>

